                '5.5' => [
                    "I'd like to talk about my English teacher, Mr. Tanaka, who had a big influence on my education. He taught me English for three years, and he was always very patient and helpful whenever I had questions in class. What made him different from other teachers was that he never made mistakes feel embarrassing — he just corrected us kindly and asked us to try again. It happened when I was in my second year that I really started to enjoy his lessons, because he often shared interesting stories and made grammar feel less boring. I felt really proud whenever he praised my progress, and that made me want to study harder. This is something I remember well, and he is the main reason I still enjoy learning English today.",
