                    "I'd like to talk about a book called 'Sapiens'. It's about the history of people, and it talks about how humans became so powerful compared to other animals. I read it two years ago during summer holidays, when I had a lot of free time. It was one of my favourite books because it explained many things I didn't know before, in a way that wasn't difficult to understand. My older brother was very patient and helpful, explaining some difficult parts to me when I got confused. This is something I remember well, and I still think about some of the ideas from it, which is why it left such a memorable impression on me.",
