                    "This was a memorable experience because learning to touch-type was really difficult for me at first. First, I could only use two fingers, which made everything slow and frustrating. Then, I found an app that encouraged me to practise a little every day, which slowly helped me feel more confident. After that, I started noticing real improvement, and I became genuinely curious about how fast I could eventually type. In the end, after about two months of daily practice, typing without looking at the keyboard felt completely natural. Looking back now, I think what helped most was having a supportive friend who kept encouraging me not to give up during the difficult early weeks.",
                    "This was a memorable experience because I helped my younger cousin with her maths homework almost every weekend for a couple of months. First, I noticed she seemed frustrated and not very confident whenever numbers were involved, so I tried to encourage her gently instead of correcting every small mistake. Then, I started using everyday examples, like shopping and cooking, to explain problems in a way that felt less abstract. After that, I could see her becoming more curious about maths instead of avoiding it. In the end, she passed an important test that she had been dreading for weeks. Looking back now, I feel proud, because it made her both more confident and genuinely curious about a subject she used to dislike.",
