                '6.5' => [
                    "It left a lasting impression on me because my English teacher, Mr. Tanaka, was always nurturing rather than strict, and looking back, I can honestly say he had a profound impact on how I see language learning. What I remember most vividly is how insightful his comments on my essays were — he never simply corrected mistakes, but explained why a phrase sounded unnatural, which genuinely helped me improve. His lessons were often thought-provoking too, since he liked connecting grammar points to real conversations he'd had while living abroad. What made him particularly different from other teachers was the resilience he tried to instil in us; whenever I gave a wrong answer, he treated it as part of the learning process rather than a failure. In hindsight, I think it was this nurturing approach, combined with his genuinely insightful feedback, that helped me stay motivated even during my most difficult year of exams, and I still think about his advice whenever I face a challenging piece of writing.",
