                    "It's honestly become something of a game-changer for me — Duolingo. What I appreciate is how versatile the app is, letting me troubleshoot my own weak points, like verb tenses, through short bursts of repeated practice rather than long, exhausting study sessions. In hindsight, gamifying language learning like this has kept me far more consistent than any textbook ever did, largely because it turns what could easily feel like a chore into something closer to a habit I look forward to. What made it particularly memorable was reaching a hundred-day streak, which felt like a small but genuine achievement. What surprised me most was how reliable the app proved to be even during busy exam periods, since the lessons are short enough to fit into almost any schedule. Looking back, I'd say it has become a genuinely indispensable tool for keeping my motivation consistent.",
                    "It left a lasting impression on me — getting lost in an unfamiliar city with no internet connection during a solo trip abroad. Thankfully, my offline maps app proved to be an indispensable tool, helping me troubleshoot my location step by step using GPS alone. What I remember most vividly is the moment of relief when the little blue dot finally appeared on the map, showing me exactly which street I was on. In hindsight, that experience made me appreciate just how versatile modern technology has become, given that it worked reliably even without a signal. What made it particularly memorable was realising afterwards how differently the evening could have gone only a few years earlier, before such tools existed. Looking back, I think of it as a small but genuine game-changer moment, since it completely removed a kind of travel anxiety I used to feel in unfamiliar places.",
                    "It could genuinely be a game-changer for me — a full smart home system. What appeals to me is how versatile it sounds, letting me troubleshoot small daily annoyances like forgetting to turn off lights or leaving the heater running by accident. In hindsight, it seems like exactly the kind of indispensable tool that would make everyday life noticeably easier, especially on busy mornings when I rush out without checking anything properly. What I find particularly appealing is that it could revolutionise something as ordinary as coming home, since lights and heating could adjust automatically before I even walk through the door. Looking back at how often I've forgotten small things in the past, I imagine it would remove a surprising amount of everyday stress. What ultimately draws me to it is less the technology itself and more the reliable peace of mind it seems to offer.",
                    "It left a lasting impression on me — my laptop crashing hours before a deadline, right when I most needed it to be reliable. I had to troubleshoot the issue quickly, trying everything from restarting to checking cables, before thankfully a friend helped me recover most of the file from an old backup. What I remember most vividly is the sinking feeling the moment the screen went black, since I genuinely thought hours of work had disappeared completely. In hindsight, it taught me how important it is to back up my work using a more versatile, reliable system, rather than trusting a single device. What made the whole experience particularly stressful was not having a backup plan at all, something I've since treated as an indispensable habit. Looking back, I'd say that crash was, in its own way, a small game-changer, since it completely changed how carefully I manage my files now.",
                ],
                '7.0' => [
                    "There's one piece of technology that really stands out for me: the note-taking app on my smartphone. What began as a simple convenience has become something genuinely transformative for my productivity, offering an almost unparalleled convenience compared with how disorganised I used to be before I started using it properly. I had never expected such a modest piece of cutting-edge software to change my habits so completely, yet within a few months it had quietly become the backbone of how I plan my entire week. What really stood out was how effortlessly it let me troubleshoot small daily inefficiencies, from missed deadlines to forgotten errands, without requiring any real effort on my part. It goes without saying that no single app constitutes a genuine technological breakthrough on its own, but the cumulative effect on my organisation has been invaluable. This experience has stayed with me ever since I first started relying on it daily, and I now find it almost impossible to imagine managing my responsibilities without it.",
                    "There's one app that really stands out in my daily routine: Duolingo. What strikes me most is how a fairly simple, cutting-edge design has had such a transformative effect on my consistency with language learning, something I had always struggled with in the past. I had never expected gamification to be the technological breakthrough that finally kept me practising daily, yet here I am, still using it more than a year later. What really stood out was the unparalleled convenience of being able to troubleshoot my weakest grammar points during small pockets of otherwise wasted time, like waiting for a bus. This experience has stayed with me, to the point where I genuinely look forward to a habit I once considered a chore, and I now find the app almost invaluable whenever I'm preparing for something like an exam. It goes without saying that no app can replace real conversation, but as a consistent daily foundation, it has proved remarkably versatile.",
                    "There's one occasion that really stands out in my memory: finding myself completely lost abroad late at night, with no way to ask for directions in a language I barely spoke. My offline map app turned out to be nothing short of a technological breakthrough in that moment, offering an unparalleled convenience that got me home safely without a single wrong turn. I had never expected something as ordinary as GPS to feel so genuinely invaluable, yet in that situation it was the only thing standing between me and a fairly stressful night. What really stood out was how the app let me troubleshoot my route in real time, adjusting instantly whenever I took a wrong turn without realising it. This experience has stayed with me as proof of how transformative the right piece of cutting-edge technology can be in a genuine crisis, however small. It goes without saying that I now never travel anywhere without downloading offline maps in advance, a habit that experience instilled in me almost immediately.",
                    "There's one piece of cutting-edge technology I'd genuinely like to try: a comprehensive smart home system that manages lighting, heating and security automatically. I suspect the impact would be quietly transformative, offering an unparalleled convenience for minor daily frustrations that most people barely notice they're putting up with, like leaving lights on or forgetting to lock the door. This is something I'd consider a technological breakthrough, at least on a personal, everyday level, given how much mental effort we spend on genuinely trivial tasks. What really stood out to me, after reading about it, was how the system could troubleshoot issues itself, alerting you to a problem before you even realise something is wrong. I had never expected something so ordinary as home security to feel invaluable, yet the more I think about it, the more convinced I am that it would meaningfully change my daily routine. This experience of researching it has stayed with me, and it goes without saying that I intend to invest in one as soon as I can genuinely afford it.",
                    "There's one occasion that really stands out in my memory: my laptop crashing just hours before an important deadline, taking what felt like an entire evening's work with it. What could have been disastrous turned into an oddly transformative lesson about backing up my work properly, largely thanks to a friend who helped me troubleshoot the issue late into the night. I had never expected something so ordinary as a hardware failure to feel so genuinely invaluable in hindsight, yet it fundamentally changed my habits around cutting-edge cloud storage. What really stood out was how close I came to losing everything, simply because I had never treated backing up my files as anything more than an afterthought. This experience has stayed with me ever since, and I've come to see reliable cloud storage as a genuinely invaluable tool rather than an unnecessary, cutting-edge luxury. It goes without saying that no piece of technology is entirely failure-proof, but the unparalleled convenience of automatic backups has made that particular crisis feel like a distant memory.",
